<TITLE> Babar secures bail in arms case, no bar to release: lawyer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com)Former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar has secured three months' interim bail in an arms case, paving the way for the BNP leader to step out of jail, his lawyer said on Tuesday. Babar has now been granted bail in all cases he faces, Ahsanul Karim said. The High Court bench of justices Sayed Mohammad Dastagir Hossain and Mohammad Raisuddin granted the bail after hearing a petition Dhaka Metropolitan Special Tribunal sentenced Babar to 17 years in jail in the case on Oct 30, 2008. Babar challenged the verdict in the High Court and applied for bail. bd
